  "market_context": "ETH 1-minute is in a bearish leg with consecutive down-close candles. Price rallies up into a T-spot zone, suggesting a potential continuation lower, but the same rally simultaneously takes out a short-term low to the downside in the prior structure.",
  "key_observation": "The retracement into the T-spot is a sharp V-shaped move, and the bearish closure through it also sweeps a short-term low — creating ambiguity about whether to short the continuation or wait for a bullish setup off the swept low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the T-spot area on the ETH 1-minute chart and look for a continuation lower from it.",
    "Step 2: Observe that price reaches up into the T-spot with quite an aggressive move, still qualifying as a V-shaped reversal.",
    "Step 3: Note that the bearish closure through the T-spot simultaneously takes out a short-term low below.",
    "Step 4: Recognize that sweeping the short-term low could engineer a bullish setup, conflicting with the bearish continuation thesis.",
    "Step 5: Decide to wait and see whether a bullish setup forms at the short-term low or whether a new bearish continuation develops instead of entering immediately."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When a continuation signal also sweeps an opposing short-term swing, the setup is conflicted. Patience is required — wait for either a bullish reaction at the swept low or a fresh continuation pattern before committing, rather than forcing an aggressive entry.",
